        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 7 at 3:40AM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 340 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles southwest of Rosita, or 11 miles northwest of Benavides, moving
northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Freer, Benavides, Seven Sisters, and Rosita.

This includes US Highway 59 between mile markers 752 and 782.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 AM CDT for
south central Texas.</instruction>
